content:
Delete unnecessary datasets to reduce app clutter and avoid reaching your org's total row limit for all registered datasets. You can delete datasets from shared apps on which you have at least Editor access, your My Private App, and another user’s My Private App with special permission.

To delete a dataset: 
- Use CRM Analytics AND Editor access to the dataset’s app
- Manage CRM Analytics Private Assets to delete in another user's My Private App

Before deletion:
- You can’t recover a deleted dataset.
- Review usage information on the dataset’s edit page to see where it is used.
- Remove references from dashboards, lenses, dataflow transformations, and recipes.

To locate the Delete Dataset button:
- In CRM Analytics home or app page: click Edit next to the dataset.
- In data manager: click Data tab, then Datasets subtab, click Edit Dataset.
title: Deleting Datasets in CRM Analytics
